The '''Battle Group of [[Yun-Harla]]''' was one of the five battle groups that served within the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] warfleet under the command of [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]] during the [[Battle of Ebaq]] 9.

==History==
When the Yuuzhan Vong arrived in the [[Star system/Legends|system]], this Battle Group was kept in reserve along with the [[Battle Group of Yun-Yuuzhan]], while the other three groups engaged the fleets of [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Traest Kre'fey]] and [[General/Legends|General]] [[Keyan Farlander/Legends|Keyan Farlander]]. When the [[Smugglers' Alliance]] arrived, they were forced into the battle. However, the tide quickly turned against the Yuuzhan Vong; Lah, after discovering the nature of the trap, was forced to order his fleets to withdraw back to [[Yuuzhan Vong empire|Yuuzhan Vong Space]]. However, the Yun-Harla group and the [[Yun-Txiin]] [[Battle Group of Yun-Txiin|battle group]] were pulled out of hyperspace and severely damaged by the mines that the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] had laid out to further hamper any retreat. Both groups suffered extreme casualties both in terms of warships and personnel as a result of the battle and subsequent evacuation.

